<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Technological Changes Since 2010</title>
</head>
<style>
    body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

header h1 {
    margin: 0;
}

article {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    padding: 0 20px;
}

section {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

h2 {
    color: #333;
}

p {
    color: #555;
}

a {
    color: #007bff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

footer {
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    color: #555;
    padding: 10px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

</style>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
    <header>
        <h1>Technological Changes Since 2010</h1>
    </header>
    <article>
        <p>
            As we venture further into the 21st century, the pace of technological advancement continues to astonish. From the rise of artificial intelligence to the proliferation of smartphones, the landscape of technology has undergone a dramatic transformation since 2010.
        </p>
        <section>
            <h2>The Mobile Revolution</h2>
            <p>
                One of the most noticeable changes has been the ubiquitous presence of smartphones. Devices like the iPhone and Android phones have become essential tools in our daily lives, reshaping how we communicate, work, and access information.
                <a href="https://www.history.com/news/the-history-of-the-smartphone-timeline">[1]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Rise of Artificial Intelligence</h2>
            <p>
                Artificial intelligence (AI) has also made significant strides since 2010. Machine learning algorithms power everything from recommendation systems on streaming platforms to autonomous vehicles, revolutionizing industries and our understanding of technology's capabilities.
                <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-00741-9">[2]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>The Internet of Things (IoT)</h2>
            <p>
                The concept of the Internet of Things has gained traction, connecting everyday objects to the internet and enabling them to communicate with each other. Smart home devices, wearables, and industrial IoT applications have all contributed to this interconnected ecosystem.
                <a href="https://www.iotforall.com/what-is-the-internet-of-things-a-complete-beginners-guide">[3]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Advancements in Renewable Energy</h2>
            <p>
                The push for sustainable technologies has led to remarkable advancements in renewable energy sources. Solar panels, wind turbines, and battery storage solutions have become more efficient and affordable, driving the shift towards a greener future.
                <a href="https://www.nrel.gov/research/re-battery.html">[4]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Blockchain and Cryptocurrencies</h2>
            <p>
                Blockchain technology, popularized by cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, has disrupted traditional financial systems. Its decentralized and secure nature has sparked innovations beyond finance, including supply chain management and digital identity verification.
                <a href="https://www.ibm.com/blockchain/what-is-blockchain">[5]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Emergence of 5G Networks</h2>
            <p>
                The rollout of 5G networks has set the stage for faster and more reliable wireless communication. This technology promises to enable innovations such as autonomous vehicles, augmented reality experiences, and enhanced Internet connectivity.
                <a href="https://www.ericsson.com/en/news/2020/10/5g-networks-beginner-guide">[6]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Challenges and Ethical Considerations</h2>
            <p>
                Alongside these advancements, there are also challenges and ethical considerations that need to be addressed. Issues such as data privacy, algorithmic bias, and the impact of automation on jobs require careful examination as technology continues to evolve.
                <a href="https://www.brookings.edu/research/artificial-intelligence-and-privacy/">[7]</a>
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
